---
---

<section id="about" class="py-24 px-6 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
  <div class="reveal">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-12">
      <span class="text-xs font-mono text-accent/70 uppercase tracking-widest">About</span>
      <div class="flex-1 h-px bg-border"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-5 gap-12 items-start">
    <!-- Text -->
    <div class="md:col-span-3 space-y-5 reveal">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold leading-tight">
        I write tools<br />
        <span class="text-accent">for people who design chips.</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
        My day job at Qualcomm is to build EDA software that supports hardware engineers across the full chip design flow, from RTL to GDS.
        I build Python systems for connectivity validation, IP release management, and design workflow automation,
        helping make complex silicon development flows more reliable, scalable, and efficient.
        My work contributes to the software infrastructure behind chips that power billions of devices worldwide.
      </p>
      <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
        On the side I've been building in the LLM space: a Text-to-SQL pipeline exploring different
        RAG strategies and LangGraph orchestration patterns, and an
        <a href="https://selimym.github.io/data_privacy_distopia/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
           class="text-accent hover:text-text transition-colors underline underline-offset-2">educational browser game</a>
        about how surveillance systems get normalized.
      </p>
      <p class="text-muted leading-relaxed">
        My interest in ML goes back to my studies. At Huawei's Mathematical and Algorithmic Sciences Lab
        I went deep into representation learning and neural network theory, working on binary neural networks
        applied to computer vision and telecommunications. While at Qualcomm I kept up with the research
        and gradually shifted focus toward LLMs and agentic systems. More recently I've been revisiting the
        systems side through MIT's TinyML and Efficient Deep Learning Computing courses and the
        <a href="https://mlsysbook.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
           class="text-accent hover:text-text transition-colors underline underline-offset-2">ML Systems book</a>,
        catching up with modern quantization, pruning, and MLOps practices.
      </p>

      <!-- Publication -->
      <a
        href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/11106423"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-3 py-2 rounded-lg bg-surface border border-border text-sm text-muted hover:border-accent/30 hover:text-text transition-colors"
      >
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-4 h-4 text-accent flex-shrink-0" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 12h6m-6 4h6m2 5H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z" />
        </svg>
        Co-author, <span class="text-text font-medium">MGOL: Molecule Generation with Ordering Loss</span> &mdash; IEEE 2025
      </a>
    </div>

    <!-- Stats -->
    <div class="md:col-span-2 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 reveal">
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-text mb-1">4<span class="text-accent">+</span></div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted">Years production Python at Qualcomm</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-text mb-1">$4<span class="text-accent">M+</span></div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted">Annual licensing costs saved</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="text-4xl font-bold text-text mb-1">140<span class="text-accent">+</span></div>
        <div class="text-sm text-muted">Chip designers using my tools</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .stat-card {
    @apply p-5 rounded-xl bg-surface border border-border hover:border-accent/30 transition-colors;
  }
</style>
